From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/eevdf: Fix place_entity() double-counting curr weight
 during reweight

When reweight_entity() is called for an entity that is cfs_rq->curr,
the subsequent place_entity() call has two bugs:

1. avg_vruntime() uses the NEW weight (already set via update_load_set)
   with the OLD vruntime, computing a wrong V.

2. The lag inflation formula adds both curr->load.weight and
   se->load.weight to the denominator. Since se == curr, this counts
   the same entity's weight twice, producing an inflation factor of
   (W + 2*w') / (W + w') instead of the correct (W + w') / W.

Combined, these errors break the lag preservation invariant: reweight
should preserve the weighted average vruntime V (Corollary #2 from
commit eab03c23c2a1), but the buggy code changes V.

Fix this by capturing V before the weight change and, for the curr
case, computing the new vruntime directly as V_old - scaled_vlag.
This avoids both the wrong-V and double-counting problems. For
non-curr entities, place_entity() remains correct because the entity
has been removed from the rb-tree, so there is no double-counting.

Fixes: 6d71a9c61604 ("sched/fair: Fix EEVDF entity placement bug causing scheduling lag")
Signed-off-by: kSTEP <kstep@kernel.org>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 21 +++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index 3eaeceda71b0..1312c5989a83 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -3755,6 +3755,7 @@ static void reweight_entity(struct cfs_rq *cfs_rq, struct sched_entity *se,
 			    unsigned long weight)
 {
 	bool curr = cfs_rq->curr == se;
+	u64 avruntime;
 
 	if (se->on_rq) {
 		/* commit outstanding execution time */
@@ -3763,6 +3764,12 @@ static void reweight_entity(struct cfs_rq *cfs_rq, struct sched_entity *se,
 		se->deadline -= se->vruntime;
 		se->rel_deadline = 1;
 		cfs_rq->nr_queued--;
+		/*
+		 * Capture V before the weight change. For curr entities we
+		 * must use this directly rather than calling place_entity(),
+		 * which would double-count curr's weight in the inflation.
+		 */
+		avruntime = avg_vruntime(cfs_rq);
 		if (!curr)
 			__dequeue_entity(cfs_rq, se);
 		update_load_sub(&cfs_rq->load, se->load.weight);
@@ -3787,7 +3794,19 @@ static void reweight_entity(struct cfs_rq *cfs_rq, struct sched_entity *se,
 
 	enqueue_load_avg(cfs_rq, se);
 	if (se->on_rq) {
-		place_entity(cfs_rq, se, 0);
+		if (curr) {
+			/*
+			 * For curr, place_entity() would compute
+			 * avg_vruntime() with the new weight (wrong V)
+			 * and inflate the lag counting curr's weight
+			 * twice. Use V from before the weight change.
+			 */
+			se->vruntime = avruntime - se->vlag;
+			se->deadline += se->vruntime;
+			se->rel_deadline = 0;
+		} else {
+			place_entity(cfs_rq, se, 0);
+		}
 		update_load_add(&cfs_rq->load, se->load.weight);
 		if (!curr)
 			__enqueue_entity(cfs_rq, se);
-- 
